(1, 'health-advocacy-and-communication-officer-haco-19-07-49', 'health-advocacy-and-communication-officer-haco-', 'job', 'Health Advocacy and Communication Officer (HACO)', NULL, '2025-04-04', '2025-04-04', '<p><strong>﻿Vacancy Announcement</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(First Time Published Notice)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>BEE-Group</strong>&nbsp;is an autonomous, independent, non-partisan, nonprofit making independent, non-governmental organization (NGO). It was established in 2000 AD, registered in the District Administration Office, Banke, and affiliated with the Social Welfare Council, Nepal. It is serving in the Lumbini and Sudurpaschim Province of Nepal for the protection and promotion of human rights, environmental conservation, climate change adaptation, disaster risk reduction, building access to quality education, health and WASH services, sustainable livelihoods, and community development. Since it is working on the rights-based approach to issues such as social justice, peace, human rights, environment conservation, sustainable livelihoods, and community development. It works to attain peace, development, and justice through people&rsquo;s meaningful participation and a bottom-up approach to establishing an equitable, healthy, and self-reliant society by building a trustworthy reputation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>BEE-Group has been implementing a Supporting Occupational and Environmental Health Project in Banke district in partnership with M&eacute;decins du Monde- France - Nepal Office. The project aims to strengthen the health system by contributing to the occupational health, promoting a healthy city, urban health, and nutrition. BEE-Group is seeking qualified, experienced, and self-motivated staff for the mentioned project and requests applications from eligible candidates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Position: Health Advocacy and Communication Officer (HACO) - One</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duty Station:</strong>&nbsp;Based at BEE-Group office, Banke and frequent visits to project areas</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reports to:</strong>&nbsp;Project Coordinator</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Supervises:</strong>&nbsp;N/A</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Job Summary:&nbsp;</strong>The Health Advocacy and Communication Officer will play a role in achieving the project outcomes by contributing to various health advocacy and communications initiatives, for the healthy city approach, environmental health initiatives, event planning, content creation, and media management. This role requires a creative and strategic thinker with strong communication skills and experience in a healthy city approach, occupational and environmental health interventions, advocacy, public relations, and stakeholder engagement. The Health Advocacy and Communication Officer will be directly responsible for establishing strong health advocacy with stakeholders and local governments along with contributing to the project components, i.e., Occupational Health, Healthy City approach, Urban Health and Nutrition by ensuring sound relationship with the community and the M&eacute;decins du Monde- France &ndash; Nepal Office.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Planning and Implementation of activities regarding Health Advocacy</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Develop and execute health advocacy plans to influence policies and practices in line with project outcomes and impact.</li>\r\n	<li>Identify and engage key stakeholders including government officials, policymakers, community leaders, and partner organizations.</li>\r\n	<li>Organize and participate in advocacy events, workshops, and campaigns to promote project objectives</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor and evaluate the effectiveness of health advocacy activities, using feedback and data to inform future strategies.</li>\r\n	<li>Prepare regular reports on communication and advocacy activities, outcomes, and impact for internal and external stakeholders.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Communication Strategy and Content Creation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Develop and implement comprehensive communication strategies to promote project goals, enhance public awareness, and support advocacy efforts.</li>\r\n	<li>Develop high-quality communication materials, including brochures, fact sheets, infographics, and videos, to effectively convey project messages.</li>\r\n	<li>Manage content for various communication channels, including social media, letters, newsletters, press releases, and reports</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure all communication materials are culturally sensitive, accurate, and aligned with the organization&#39;s branding guidelines</li>\r\n	<li>Build and maintain relationships with media outlets and journalists to ensure adequate coverage of project initiatives and achievements</li>\r\n	<li>Draft and distribute press releases, media briefs, and opinion pieces to highlight project achievements and key messages</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor media coverage and analyze its impact on public perception and advocacy efforts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Stakeholder Engagement</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Assist in organizing internal events, campaigns, and initiatives that promote employee participation and morale</li>\r\n	<li>Foster and maintain relationships with stakeholders to build a network of support for project initiatives</li>\r\n	<li>Coordinate meetings, briefings, and consultations with stakeholders to discuss project progress and advocacy priorities</li>\r\n	<li>Represent the organization at relevant forums, conferences, and events</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Project Implementation and Management</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Responsible for the quality implementation of SOEH project health interventions including healthy city approach, environmental and urban health interventions as per donor guidance and compliances</li>\r\n	<li>Work in coordination with the government and line agencies to implement the project in targeted sites and to foster long-term impact and visibility</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure that the implementation methods are as per the guidelines developed and acknowledged with good practice and that they achieve sustainable results</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure that the ground-level issues are reported accordingly to the responsible line to resolve any issues affecting the program</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor the project activities in the field regularly to ensure maximum results of the implemented activities, and follow up the identified issues for correction</li>\r\n	<li>Support initiatives to enhance beneficiaries&#39; and communities&#39; accessibility to and utilization of high-quality healthcare services, adhering to OHS and public health guidelines validated by the MdM Nepal Mission.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Professional Competencies</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Develop, implement, and evaluate health advocacy and communication strategies</li>\r\n	<li>Familiar with healthy city approach, urban health components, and environmental health intervention</li>\r\n	<li>Plan and execute health advocacy campaigns</li>\r\n	<li>Write, edit, and produce content (letter, press releases, social media posts, reports, speeches).</li>\r\n	<li>Experience with multimedia production and digital storytelling</li>\r\n	<li>Establish networks with diverse stakeholders, media, and handle media inquiries</li>\r\n	<li>Knowledge of website management and online content strategies</li>\r\n	<li>Familiarity with graphic design software</li>\r\n	<li>Commitment to promoting diversity and inclusion in all communication and advocacy efforts</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to handle confidential information with discretion</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Qualifications and Experiences</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Academic requirement\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Bachelor&#39;s degree in Public Health or Nursing</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Minimum of 3 years of experience in public health-related projects, especially in urban health, occupational health, and/or environmental health including monitoring, evaluation, communication, advocacy and research.</li>\r\n	<li>Experience in developing and implementing successful health advocacy and communication strategies would be an asset</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team, with a proactive and results-oriented approach</li>\r\n	<li>Strong willingness to work with diverse communities, farmers&#39; groups, and less advantaged /marginalized communities</li>\r\n	<li>Willingness to travel to project sites and work outside regular office hours as needed.</li>\r\n	<li>Fluency in Nepali and English</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Interested candidates who meet the criteria are requested to send their application according to BEE Group&#39;s Job application form (Find the application form in the vacancy notice) and send it to&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://gmail.com/\">beegroup.vacancy@gmail.com</a></strong>&nbsp;by&nbsp;<strong>Monday, March 10, 2025, before 5:00 PM</strong>. The names of two referees with contact details must be written on the application form.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&amp;id=1129kxsWE2eH9Rba9ROhngOwocePrVuvZ\">BEE Group-Application-Form</a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Encourage people from disadvantaged and marginalized communities (Women, Dalit, Janajati, Madhesi, Muslims, and People with disabilities) to apply. Local candidates will be given high priority. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted for further process. Telephone inquiries shall not be entertained.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Candidates applying for a job with BEE-Group must be ready to comply with our Child Protection Policy and Safeguarding Policy on Preventing Harassment, Sexual Exploitation, and Abuse.</p>', 'HACO _vacancy _1.JPG', '0316f7c4b97ccc8a2e6e3ed979129a2f.JPG', 'images/work-with-us/0316f7c4b97ccc8a2e6e3ed979129a2f.JPG', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Health Advocacy and Communication Officer (HACO)', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, '2025-03-05 01:07:49', '2025-03-05 01:07:49'),
(2, 'field-facilitator-agriculture-technician-19-11-41', 'field-facilitator-agriculture-technician-', 'job', 'Field Facilitator (Agriculture Technician)', NULL, '2025-04-04', '2025-04-04', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>﻿Vacancy Announcement</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(First Time Published Notice)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>BEE-Group</strong>&nbsp;is an autonomous, independent, non-partisan, nonprofit making independent, non-governmental organization (NGO). It was established in 2000 AD, registered in the District Administration Office, Banke, and affiliated with the Social Welfare Council, Nepal. It is serving in the Lumbini and Sudurpaschim Province of Nepal for the protection and promotion of human rights, environmental conservation, climate change adaptation, disaster risk reduction, building access to quality education health and WASH services, sustainable livelihoods, and community development. Since it is working on the rights-based approach to issues such as social justice, peace, human rights, environment conservation, sustainable livelihoods, and community development. It works to attain peace, development, and justice through peoples&rsquo; meaningful participation and a bottom-up approach to establishing an equitable, healthy, and self-reliant society by building a trustworthy reputation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>BEE-Group has been implementing a EU-funded project named CSO Actions for Resilient Ecosystem and Community (Samvardhan) in partnership with ADRA Nepal with objectives to contribute in improving the biodiversity, well-being of the targeted Community Forest Users Groups and farmers of Rapti Sonari Rural Municipality, Kohalpur Municipality of Banke district and Madhuban Municipality and Thakurbaba Municipality of Bardiya district through CFUG strengthening, wild-life resistant farming, forest, farm and ecotourism based enterprise development, and policy advocacy and support to strengthen the local capacity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>BEE-Group is seeking qualified, experienced, and self-motivated staff for the mentioned project and requests for applications from eligible candidates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Position: Field Facilitator (Agriculture Technician) &ndash; One&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duty Station: One of the projects implementing Palika of Banke district 100% field base</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Job Summary:&nbsp;</strong>The Field Facilitator (Agriculture Technician) will play a vital role in social mobilization and providing technical support to the farmer&#39;s group for the implementation of activities in the field to achieve the objectives stated in the project document inconsistent with the strategic direction of BEE-Group thereby making a major contribution to the development and articulation of the organization&rsquo;s objectives. The Field Facilitator will report to the project coordinator and work in close coordination with the consortium partner&#39;s staff in the field. The Field Facilitator will be responsible for carrying out the activity implementation with the highest degree of targeted community engagement and building relationships with like-minded stakeholders for the smooth implementation of project interventions.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Major Task and Responsibility</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lead in the smooth implementation of the project activities in the field as per activity implementation guidelines mobilizing farmer&#39;s groups, community forest user groups, and relevant stakeholders providing necessary support in community mobilization for enterprise development and establishment and expansion of climate-smart technology for sustainable livelihoods.&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Identification, selection, and if necessary, formation of farmer&#39;s groups and facilitate them for the institutional development and provide regular technical backstopping support.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure effective and efficient implementation of the community mobilization for carrying out the project activities in a timely manner through Social Behaviour Change Communication.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Prepare, participate, and conduct training, and workshops, and support the project coordinator for facilitation to establish and functionalize farmer&#39;s group and community forest user group.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure quality delivery of project activities/inputs as planned way and perform regular field visits to ensure the smooth implementation of project activities in the field.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Support in the development of required technical manuals, guidelines, and resource materials for community mobilization and conduction of technical training and workshops related to climate-smart agriculture practices and introducing climate-smart technology.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Support and facilitate for planning and implementation of project activities properly, ensuring the implementation in the field timely manner.</li>\r\n	<li>Support to admin and finance department for proper management of financial transactions referring to the compliances.</li>\r\n	<li>Support to project coordinator in documentation and compilation of quantitative data and qualitative information from the field.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Work closely maintaining the professional relationship with the local government, farmers groups, community forest user groups, and relevant stakeholders.</li>\r\n	<li>Promotion of a conductive environment through networking and workshops with stakeholders involving public, and private partnerships (PPP), including ward-level and municipal-level government.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Facilitate the newly formed or non-registered farmer&#39;s group for registration at the local government and advocacy for tapping the local government resources to expand climate-smart technologies and improve agriculture practices in the field.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Contribute to the active participation of targeted project participants in the activity implementation and support in building their capacity and leading farmers to collectively engage them for the resolution of identified issues regarding climate change and human-wildlife conflict.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>If required, Support and facilitate the Forest user&#39;s group, and local entrepreneurs in promoting forest-based enterprise and marketing to diversify livelihood opportunities and sustainability.&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Follow up on the relevant guidelines and reference documents designed by the consortium partner organization and BEE Group in collaboration.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Education and Experience:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Intermediate in Agriculture Science with 3 years of relevant experience in working with I/NGOs in similar fields or Junior Technical/Assistant in Agriculture with 5 years of relevant experience in working with I/NGOs in similar fields.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Well familiar with the locality and communities of Banke and Bardiya districts will be an advantage.</li>\r\n	<li>Proven knowledge and experience in project activities planning, and implementation, database recording, and reporting.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Strong willingness to work with diverse communities, farmers&#39; groups, and less advantaged /marginalized communities.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Proven knowledge and experience in working with consortium organizations and government authorities.</li>\r\n	<li>Reporting written skills and data collection using the applications.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Good communication skills with communities and stakeholders.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Interested candidates who meet the criteria are requested to send their application according to&nbsp;<strong>BEE Group&#39;s Job application form (Find the application form in the vacancy notice)&nbsp;</strong>and send it to&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://gmail.com/\">beegroup.vacancy@gmail.com</a></strong>&nbsp;by<strong>&nbsp;Sunday, March 9, 2025, before 5:00 PM.&nbsp;</strong>The names of two referees with contact details must be written on the application form.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Link:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&amp;id=1129kxsWE2eH9Rba9ROhngOwocePrVuvZ\">Application Form</a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Encourage people from disadvantaged and marginalized communities (Women, Dalit, Janajati, Madhesi, Muslims, and People with disabilities) to apply. Local candidates will be given high priority.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted for further process. Telephone inquiries shall not be entertained.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Candidates applying for a job with BEE-Group must be ready to comply with our Child Protection Policy and Safeguarding Policy on Preventing Harassment, Sexual Exploitation, and Abuse.</em></p>', 'HACO _vacancy _2.JPG', '0c569f5969a44872027b621a3056fd32.JPG', 'images/work-with-us/0c569f5969a44872027b621a3056fd32.JPG', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Field Facilitator (Agriculture Technician)', 'Muslims, People with disabilities, Madhesi', 'Encourage people from disadvantaged and marginalized communities (Women, Dalit, Janajati, Madhesi, Muslims, and People with disabilities) to apply. Local candidates will be given high priority.', 0, 1, 1, NULL, '2025-03-05 01:11:41', '2025-03-05 01:11:41');

